  "summary": "Malicious code in tick-forge (npm)",
  "details": "Tick-forge@11.5.2 is a combosquat of the legitimate tickforge package. On import, it fetches a remote payload from 31[.]97[.]137[.]157:45000/icons/107 over HTTPS and executes the response via new Function() with full Node.js globals (require, process, Buffer), enabling arbitrary remote code execution. The README describes a fake trading toolkit that does not match the actual behaviour.",
